        <mxCell id="9zhOEuiz0M9-8aL9bN6m-32" parent="1" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;fontColor=#000000;darkOpacity=0.05;fillColor=#FFF9B2;strokeColor=none;fillStyle=solid;direction=west;gradientDirection=north;gradientColor=#FFF2A1;shadow=1;size=20;pointerEvents=1;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237));&quot;&gt;The logical topology shown above highlights key aspects of the configured network, including:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Device Hostnames&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Link Aggregation Connections using Fiber&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237));&quot;&gt;IP address connections between devices&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237));&quot;&gt;DHCP was configured on Juniper to ensure devices connected to the network could automatically receive an IP address&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;OSPF zones showcased in Blue, Green, Orange, and Gray, labeled Area 116, 0, 16, and 216 respectively.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;EIGRP zone showcased in Red.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Syslog, TFTP, and LibreNMS SMTP was additionally configured on the TFTP server.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
